Consider this TypeScript code:

```typescript
interface Animal {
  name: string;
  speak(): string;
}
```

What does the interface `Animal` define?

Consider this TypeScript code:

```typescript
class Car {
  brand: string;

  constructor(brand: string) {
    this.brand = brand;
  }
}
```

`brand` is an instance variable.

Consider this TypeScript code:

```typescript
class Animal {
  move(): string {
    return "moving";
  }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
  bark(): string {
    return "woof";
  }
}
```

Why can `Dog` use the `move()` method?

